Attempt to invoke virtual method 'java.lang.String android.net.Uri.getScheme()' on a null object reference
comes from Android’s Intent system when you pass an invalid or null URI to Share.open().
This usually happens because:

The file wasn’t fully downloaded before being shared.

The path (file://...) is incorrect or missing.

On Android 10+, you need to use RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath or RNFS.CachesDirectoryPath — not every folder allows file sharing anymore.

Notes

Use CachesDirectoryPath or DocumentDirectoryPath

RNFS.CachesDirectoryPath works best for temporary files you just want to share.

On Android 10+ (Scoped Storage), some directories can’t be shared.

Always prefix with file://

url: 'file://' + localPath


Ensure file exists before sharing

const exists = await RNFS.exists(localPath);


Add permissions (Android only)
Make sure your AndroidManifest.xml has:

<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />